Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} on to boil.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and @onion{1}(chopped), then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until the mince is browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{150%ml} for the sauce, @tomato puree{30%g}, @red wine jus paste{22%g} and @mixed herbs{1}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir occasionally and reduce the heat if necessary.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the saucepan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{splash} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Once the mince filling has thickened, spoon into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the mash. Spread out in an even layer, then sprinkle over the cheese.

Bake the pie on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While the pie cooks, wash out your potato pan, then fill it with water and bring to the boil on high heat. Trim the @green beans{80%g}.

When the pie has ~{5%minutes} of cooking time left, add the beans and @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boiling water. Bring the pan back to the boil and cook until just tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Drain in a colander, then return to the saucepan.

Season with salt and pepper. Toss in @?olive oil{} if you'd like.

When ready, spoon the cheesy mash pie onto your plates.

Serve with the green beans alongside.

Enjoy!